3) key concepts.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course aims to provide practical knowledge and skills to apply interdisciplinary approaches to understand, analyse and guide national and local developments and economic processes in new sustainability policies and contexts.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) understands economic processes at different levels, is able to analyse economic processes and systems, is able to make connections between economic and business relationships; 2) can identify economic problems, risks and opportunities using analytical methods and propose solutions; 3) can apply economic knowledge of the main economic concepts and approaches in economic analysis and economic evaluation of strategies, plans and projects; 4) can express the results of the analysis in a professional and convincing manner.
